Package graph.algorithms.planarity

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BoyerMyrvoldPlanarity<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    The Boyer-Myrvold algorithm is a planarity testing algorithm which uses reverse DFS order as numbering of the vertices of G.
    Embedding<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>  
    FraysseixMendezPlanarity<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    An algorithm for checking the planarity of a graph based on Fraysseix and Mendez's algorithm
    MaximumPlanaritySubgraph<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    A widely used standard heuristic for finding a maximal planar subgraph is to start with a spanning tree of G, and to iteratively try to add the remaining edges one by one In every step, a planarity testing algorithm is called for the obtained graph.
    PlanarEmbedding  
    PlanarFaces<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    For each edge, there should be a right and a left face If (v,w) is an edge, the left face is the one that contains (v,w) and the right face is the one that contains (w,v)
    PlanarityTestingAlgorithm<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>  
    PQTreePlanarity<V extends Vertex,E extends Edge<V>>
    PQ tree planarity testing based on Booth and Lueker's algorithm
